Three White Soldiers

    Definition: A bullish continuation/reversal pattern with three long bullish candles, each closing higher than the previous, often after a downtrend.
    Criteria:
        All three candles: Bullish (close > open), with each close > previous close.
        Each candle: Body ≥ 60% of range (high - low), minimal shadows.
    What It Tells a Trader:
        Strong Bullish Momentum: Signals sustained buying pressure, either continuing an uptrend or reversing a downtrend.
        Context-Dependent: Effective at support levels or after consolidation.
    How to Trade It:
        Entry: Long at the third candle’s close or on a pullback to the third candle’s open.
        Stop-Loss: Below the first candle’s low (1-2x atr14).
        Take-Profit: Next resistance (2-3x risk).
        Confirmation: RSI > 50, ADX > 25, high volume_surge_ratio, order_book_imbalance > 0.5.
        Futures Notes: Low leverage, confirm trend strength, monitor bid_ask_spread.